  "type": "spr",
  "stem": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the radius of the circle in the <em>xy</em>-plane defined by <math alttext=\"left parenthesis x plus 2 right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y plus 5 right parenthesis squared equals 169\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>169</mn></math>? &nbsp;</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "13"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13\"><mn>13</mn></math>. The equation of a circle in the <em>x</em><em>y</em>-plane can be written in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus k right parenthesis squared equals r squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis h comma k right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is the center of the circle and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> is the radius of the circle. It&rsquo;s given that the circle in the <em>x</em><em>y</em>-plane is defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x plus 2 right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y plus 5 right parenthesis squared equals 169\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>169</mn></math>. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r squared equals 169\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>169</mn></math>. Taking the positive square root of both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r equals 13\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn></math>. Thus, the radius of the circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13\"><mn>13</mn></math>.</p>",
